            <Title>垄断Monopolies</Title>
            <Text>A monopoly is a market structure in which only one producer or seller exists for a product. This domination of a market for a particular product or service by a single company tends to lead to restricted levels of competition and artificially high prices on a sustained basis. Typically the product has no close substitutes for consumers to switch to.
Monopolies are characterized by the following:
One firm supplies the market with many buyers and sellers.
The product is unique.
The firm has strong pricing power.
Entry into the market is restricted in some manner.
垄断是一个市场结构，其中只有一个生产者或销售者存在一个产品。 一家公司对某一特定产品或服务的市场统治倾向于导致竞争水平受限，人为地高价格持续下去。 通常情况下，该产品没有接近消费者转向的替代品。
垄断的特点如下：
一家公司为市场提供了许多买家和卖家。
该产品是独一无二的。
该公司具有强大的定价能力。
进入市场受到某种限制。</Text>
