            <Title>规模经济Economies of scale</Title>
            <Text>The advantages that economies of scale bring to businesses are extremely important to most companies. One need look no farther than Gillette or Coca-Cola to see the benefits of a large, dependable manufacturing division, coupled with an efficient distribution system. Gillette has an approximate 70% share of the global wet shaving market. It would not have been able to achieve this level of dominance without an efficient manufacturing process and the ability to ship its products globally on an affordable basis. As was stated earlier about Coca-Cola, any company trying to match Gillette would have to spend billions of dollars to match its economies of scale.
规模经济给企业带来的好处对于大多数企业来说是非常重要的。 为了看到一个大的，可靠的生产部门的好处，再加上一个高效的分销系统，人们不用再看吉列和可口可乐了。 吉列拥有全球湿剃市场约70％的份额。 如果没有高效的制造工艺和以负担得起的方式在全球范围内运输产品的能力，就不可能达到这个水平。 正如前面关于可口可乐所说的，任何试图与吉列相匹敌的公司都必须花费数十亿美元来匹配其规模经济。</Text>
