            <Title>需求效应和收入效应Substitution and income effects</Title>
            <Text>Substitutes are goods that experience an increase in demand when a similar product increases in price. A fall in the price of a commodity, or good, generally has two effects on a consumer’s income:
Substitution effect: The consumer enjoys an increase in real purchasing power since he or she can now buy the same amount of the product as before with less money, thus having money left over for additional expenditures or savings.
Income effect: The consumer could conceivably use more of a good that has become less expensive and not use as much of the goods that are now somewhat more expensive.
Although these effects occur simultaneously, a distinction can be made between the two effects. The substitution effect measures the change in the purchase of a good, resulting only from the change in the price of the good. In this case the utility (i.e., the satisfaction that the consumer receives from the good) remains constant, even though the price has changed.
替代品是指类似产品价格上涨时需求增加的产品。 商品价格的下跌通常对消费者的收入有两个影响：
替代效应：消费者的实际购买力增加了，因为他现在可以用较少的钱购买相同数量的产品，从而剩下的钱用于额外的支出或储蓄。
收入效应：消费者可以想象使用更多的价格更便宜的商品，而不是使用现在更昂贵的商品。
虽然这些效应是同时发生的，但是可以区分这两种效应。 替代效应衡量的是购买商品的变化，只是由于商品价格的变化。 在这种情况下，即使价格已经改变，效用（即消费者从商品中得到的满意度）也保持不变。

